tea-tree
Homonym Number:
Word Class: noun
Sense Number:  1
Definition:a scrubby bush, manuka (Leptospernum spp), often used to add flavour to billy tea.


Origin: [none]
Register:
Register 2:
Flag: Farm Words
Domain: Rural
Region: [none]
See: ti-tree
Pronunciation:
Notes:	nb see also ti-tree, incl fig: in the tea-tree
